The two boys aged one year eight months and four years, were presented to Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu by the State Director of the Service, Muhammad Kaumi at the Government House this Sunday. The State Director informed the Governor that, one man and four ladies were apprehended for the offence and investigation was ongoing. The five suspects were also displayed before the Governor and newsmen. They are Moses from Zuru Kebbi state, who is the main suspect, Comfort Nwanko, Matron from Usman Danfodio University Teaching Hospital (UDUTH), Helen Samuel business woman in Sokoto but from Delta and Uchenna Chikanso from Anambra live in Enugu as well as Dorothy Ikenna from Anambra state. Muhammadu Kaumi was also together with the parents Hussaini who was re-united with them. In response Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu commended the Department of State Services for a job well-done by bursting the kidnap ring, extending similar commendation to other security agencies for their untiring effort to fighting crime in the state. Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu affirmed that, Justice would take its course and warned against attaching religious or tribal sentiment to issues of criminality. Abubakar Muâ€™azu Dakingari Chief Press Secretary Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA